  <body>
    <section name="Create document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to create a document type, to define the structure
                              of a class of similar documents.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=0;
    toppx=160;
    bottompx=610;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_T07/inars/create_documenttype.png" alt='Create document type screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
     The <a href='../../contributors/concepts/folder_action_menu.html'>folder action menu</a> for
     the folder snp is popped up. The snp folder is a namespace folder. You can choose to create a new
     <a href='../concepts/documenttype.html'>document type</a> or a new
     <a href='../concepts/compoundtype.html'>compound type</a>, which is a building block for a document type.
     Dialog windows for the
     <a href='specify_type_details.html'>details</a> and the
     <a href='specify_type_layout.html'>layout</a> of the new type will appear.
     The new document type will be added to the document types in the snp namespace,
     which are now 'myhobby' and 'upcoming'.
    </p>
   </div>

